        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You were a trained killer.  When the Pentagon was through with you, the CIA put you to work in Eastern Europe. When that dried up you became a mercenary in South America, but you didn't die in the jungle... you died on your way back to the USA.  As your transport vessel docked in Los Angeles a pack of Black Hand vampires boarded in force and slaughtered everyone they found.  You were embraced that night as the Sabbat ravaged the boat for a strange relic your commanding officer had discovered in the rain forest. Even before you were embraced, the small stone statue wihspered to you, and unbeknowst to your sabbat pack it taught you the secrets of infernalism and the Path of Evil Revelations.  When the inquisition discoered your pack had the relic you were all ordered to return to Mexico City for questioning.  That's when you betrayed your pack to the Camarilla and led them into a trap set by a a powerful Tremere Archon named Ulgan Bey.  Your sire escaped with the relic that opened your eyes to the true power in this world, the demons that pull strings behind the facade of vampiric control.  While many in the Camarilla know of your Sabbat past, your dedication to the infernal powers is a secret you've kept deep within.  You've sought no converts, only the power to emulate your demonic masters and serve them when they reveal themsleves and take possession of this world."
